Hi,

 > Any other thoughts, suggestions, or references would be
 > appreciated.

In

L. S. Completions of \mu-algebras. APAL, 154(1):27-50, May 2008.

I studied the problem of the completeness of the modal mu-calculus from=20
an finitary algebraic point of view. In that paper some categorical=20
ideas, mainly from

W. Tholen, Pro-categories and multiadjoint functors, Canad. J. Math. 36=20
(1) (1984) 144=96155.

play the relevant role. The challenge is to prove that in free modal=20
\mu-algebras, the relation

\mu.f =3D \bigvee_{n>=3D0}  f^n(\bot)

holds -- where \mu.f, the least fixpoint of f, is axiomatized by=20
equational implications and free modal \mu-algebras are not known to be=20
complete.

Best,

	Luigi

