On Wed, Sep 17, 2008 at 01:13:21PM -0400, Andre Joyal wrote:

> Is it the time for a new Bourbaki?

Do we imagine this new Bourbaki as just systematizing and
presenting what we know already, or struggling to create
brand new mathematics?

I can imagine a new Bourbaki who tries to explain all of
mathematics in the language of categories.  But I can
also imagine a new Bourbaki who tries to explain all of
mathematics in the language of infinity-categories.  It
may be a bit too late for the first one, and a bit too
early for the second one.

Perhaps we need both!

