In my last post I said that sketches give rise to forgetful functors into
Set, which is obviously wrong -- the forgetful functor arising from a
given sketch is into the functor category [A,Set], where A is the
underlying category of the sketch, and this forgetful functor doesn't
determine the sketch up to isomorphism.

Mark




